// Whitespace-significant arithmetic.
//
// Operators with no surrounding whitespace bind tighter than operators with
// whitespace, regardless of the usual `*` / `+` precedence.

print(1 + 2*3)!   // 7  -- `*` is tight, `+` is loose
print(1+2 * 3)!   // 9  -- `+` is tight, `*` is loose

// Number names are real, and they obey the same rules.
print(one + two)!  // 3

// Fractions just work.
const const half = 1/2!
print(half)!      // 0.5
